            "type": "section",
            "html": "A houndmaster is responsible for the care of the tribe\u2019s pets, frequently polar bears, wolves, and winter wolves. She is fond of pitting her charges against each other, allowing the packs to establish a functional hierarchy and ensuring that only the strongest survive to breed. Some houndmasters choose these pack leaders as animal companions."
